<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,852]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,337,151,180]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The combination of metafemoral armature (
<figureCitation box="[927,1006,152,180]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="19.[151,256,1573,1597]" captionTargetBox="[163,1418,187,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,172,1552]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male metafemur. (a) Leptobasis candelaria, Belize, Toledo, Monkey River; (b) L. guanacaste, paratype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (c) L. vacillans, Dominican Republic, Jarabacoa." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194873/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[990,1006,152,180]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
a) and convoluted, foliate cercus (
<figureCitation box="[160,267,192,220]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="27.[151,256,1327,1351]" captionTargetBox="[154,1425,183,1295]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,180,1306]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 20. Male S 10, medio-dorsal view. (a) Leptobasis buchholzi, Colombia, Puerto Colombia; (b) L. candelaria, Belize, Toledo, Monkey River; (c) L. guanacaste, holotype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (d) L. lucifer, Costa Rica, Heredia, Finca La Selva; (e) L. mauffrayi, holotype, Peru, Madre de Dios, Pakitza; (f) L. melinogaster, USA, Texas, Hidalgo, Santa Ana Natural Wildlife Reserve; (g) L. raineyi, Trinidad, St. Andrew, 1 mi W of Cumuto; (h) L. vacillans, Puerto Rico, Mayagüez, Mayagüez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194881/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs. 
<number box="[233,267,192,220]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
b, 
<number box="[298,330,192,220]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="21.0">21</number>
b) will distinguish males from all others except for 
<taxonomicName box="[993,1173,192,220]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guanacaste">
<emphasis box="[993,1173,192,220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L. guanacaste</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The proximal large metafemoral spur of 
<taxonomicName box="[420,594,232,260]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis box="[420,594,232,260]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L. candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[612,689,232,260]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="19.[151,256,1573,1597]" captionTargetBox="[163,1418,187,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,172,1552]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male metafemur. (a) Leptobasis candelaria, Belize, Toledo, Monkey River; (b) L. guanacaste, paratype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (c) L. vacillans, Dominican Republic, Jarabacoa." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194873/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[673,689,232,260]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
a) is not as long as that of 
<taxonomicName box="[1031,1212,232,260]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guanacaste">
<emphasis box="[1031,1212,232,260]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L. guanacaste</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1229,1305,232,260]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="19.[151,256,1573,1597]" captionTargetBox="[163,1418,187,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,172,1552]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 5. Male metafemur. (a) Leptobasis candelaria, Belize, Toledo, Monkey River; (b) L. guanacaste, paratype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (c) L. vacillans, Dominican Republic, Jarabacoa." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194873/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1290,1305,232,260]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
b) and the shape of the cerci differ between the two species. The ventro-basal process in 
<taxonomicName box="[1221,1404,272,300]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis box="[1221,1404,272,300]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L. candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is projected ventro-posteriorly and is visible in medio-dorsal view when the cerci are spread (
<figureCitation box="[1309,1404,312,340]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="27.[151,256,1327,1351]" captionTargetBox="[154,1425,183,1295]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,180,1306]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 20. Male S 10, medio-dorsal view. (a) Leptobasis buchholzi, Colombia, Puerto Colombia; (b) L. candelaria, Belize, Toledo, Monkey River; (c) L. guanacaste, holotype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (d) L. lucifer, Costa Rica, Heredia, Finca La Selva; (e) L. mauffrayi, holotype, Peru, Madre de Dios, Pakitza; (f) L. melinogaster, USA, Texas, Hidalgo, Santa Ana Natural Wildlife Reserve; (g) L. raineyi, Trinidad, St. Andrew, 1 mi W of Cumuto; (h) L. vacillans, Puerto Rico, Mayagüez, Mayagüez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194881/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1369,1404,312,340]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
b); this structure is ventrally curved and hidden from view when the cercus is viewed medio-dorsally in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,330,392,420]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guanacaste">
<emphasis box="[151,330,392,420]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L. guanacaste</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[346,441,392,420]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="27.[151,256,1327,1351]" captionTargetBox="[154,1425,183,1295]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,180,1306]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 20. Male S 10, medio-dorsal view. (a) Leptobasis buchholzi, Colombia, Puerto Colombia; (b) L. candelaria, Belize, Toledo, Monkey River; (c) L. guanacaste, holotype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (d) L. lucifer, Costa Rica, Heredia, Finca La Selva; (e) L. mauffrayi, holotype, Peru, Madre de Dios, Pakitza; (f) L. melinogaster, USA, Texas, Hidalgo, Santa Ana Natural Wildlife Reserve; (g) L. raineyi, Trinidad, St. Andrew, 1 mi W of Cumuto; (h) L. vacillans, Puerto Rico, Mayagüez, Mayagüez." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194881/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[405,441,392,420]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
c). Females of 
<taxonomicName box="[625,797,392,420]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis box="[625,797,392,420]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L. candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[858,1037,392,420]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guanacaste">
<emphasis box="[858,1037,392,420]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L. guanacaste</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are unique in having the dorsal margin of ovipositor concave in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[731,835,432,460]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,255,1251,1275]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,199,1216]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,194,1230]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Female S 7 – 10, lateral view. (a) Leptobasis candelaria, Belize, Toledo, Monkey River; (b) L. guanacaste, allotype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (c) L. lucifer, Mexico, Campeche, Laguna Zoh; (d) L. mauffrayi, allotype, Peru, Madre de Dios, Pakitza; (e) L. raineyi, Trinidad, St. George, Indian Walk Ride; (f) L. vacillans, Mexico, Morelos, La Fuente." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194880/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs. 
<number box="[803,835,432,460]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
a, b); this structure is linear in all other species (
<figureCitation box="[160,266,472,500]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="26.[151,255,1251,1275]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,199,1216]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,194,1230]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 19. Female S 7 – 10, lateral view. (a) Leptobasis candelaria, Belize, Toledo, Monkey River; (b) L. guanacaste, allotype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (c) L. lucifer, Mexico, Campeche, Laguna Zoh; (d) L. mauffrayi, allotype, Peru, Madre de Dios, Pakitza; (e) L. raineyi, Trinidad, St. George, Indian Walk Ride; (f) L. vacillans, Mexico, Morelos, La Fuente." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194880/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Figs. 
<number box="[234,266,472,500]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
c–f). The female of 
<taxonomicName box="[524,697,472,500]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis box="[524,697,472,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L. candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the unique morphology of its prothoracic hind lobe; its middle lobe is expanded with lateral margins angulate and overlying a smaller inferior margin (
<figureCitation box="[261,340,552,580]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1702,1726]" captionText="FIGURE 2. Female pronotum, dorsal view. (a) Leptobasis buchholzi, paratype, Venezuela, Guárico, Pericoco [redrawn from a draft by J. De Marmels]; (b) L. candelaria, female, Belize, Toledo, Monkey River; (c) L. guanacaste, paratype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (d) L. lucifer, Mexico, Campeche, Laguna Zoh; (e) L. mauffrayi, allotype, Peru, Manu, Pakitza; (f) L. melinogaster, USA, Texas, Kleberg, King Ranch; (g) L. raineyi, Trinidad, St. George, Indian Walk Ride; (h) L. vacillans, Cuba, Cienfuegos, E of Pepito Rey." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[322,340,552,580]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
b). In 
<taxonomicName box="[419,602,552,580]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guanacaste">
<emphasis box="[419,602,552,580]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L. guanacaste</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the hind lobe is upright, of even width, and its lateral arms are deflexed ventrally diverging from the carinate propleural extension (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1116,592,620]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1702,1726]" captionText="FIGURE 2. Female pronotum, dorsal view. (a) Leptobasis buchholzi, paratype, Venezuela, Guárico, Pericoco [redrawn from a draft by J. De Marmels]; (b) L. candelaria, female, Belize, Toledo, Monkey River; (c) L. guanacaste, paratype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (d) L. lucifer, Mexico, Campeche, Laguna Zoh; (e) L. mauffrayi, allotype, Peru, Manu, Pakitza; (f) L. melinogaster, USA, Texas, Kleberg, King Ranch; (g) L. raineyi, Trinidad, St. George, Indian Walk Ride; (h) L. vacillans, Cuba, Cienfuegos, E of Pepito Rey." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1098,1116,592,620]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
c). Mature individuals of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,332,632,660]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candelaria">
<emphasis box="[151,332,632,660]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L. candelaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have broad mid-dorsal and humeral dark stripes and the pale postocular spots are round (
<figureCitation box="[245,319,672,700]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1606,1630]" captionTargetBox="[229,1344,194,1567]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[227,1360,175,1582]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 1. Head, dorsal view of right half. (a) Leptobasis candelaria, male, Mexico, Veracruz, E of Córdoba; (b) L. guanacaste, male paratype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (c) L. mauffrayi, male holotype, Peru, Manu, Pakitza; (d) L. vacillans, male, Dominican Republic, La Vega, S of La Vega." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194871/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[306,319,672,700]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
a); in mature 
<taxonomicName box="[498,680,672,700]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guanacaste">
<emphasis box="[498,680,672,700]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">L. guanacaste</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the dark antehumeral stripe is lacking and the postocular spots are represented by narrow pale triangles (
<figureCitation box="[755,828,712,740]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="17.[151,255,1606,1630]" captionTargetBox="[229,1344,194,1567]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[227,1360,175,1582]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 1. Head, dorsal view of right half. (a) Leptobasis candelaria, male, Mexico, Veracruz, E of Córdoba; (b) L. guanacaste, male paratype, Costa Rica, Guanacaste, Hacienda Taboga; (c) L. mauffrayi, male holotype, Peru, Manu, Pakitza; (d) L. vacillans, male, Dominican Republic, La Vega, S of La Vega." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/194871/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[815,828,712,740]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,852]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
